comment: Don't be nervous, just walk in and tell the dispatcher that you need to use a safe restroom. They will then buzz you through the door and into a small waiting room. There is a safe bathroom here. You do not need to have the dispatcher unlock the door when exiting, they automatically open when leaving the building. Remember to thank the dispatcher when you go!

comment: Our business (it looks like an art deco home) is LGBT friendly and the restroom is also handicapped accessible.  We are usually around between 8AM to 5PM CST.  If there is a car parked directly in front of the house, someone is here.  Please knock on the door loudly - we have security cameras in place so please be patient with us if we do not know you personally (no offense)!  :)

name: Thomson House (PGSS McGill)
directions: Thomson House has all-gender washrooms on the fourth floor.
comment:
You have to be a McGill graduate student, medical student or law student.

The building is also wheelchair accessible, but access is limited by the nature of its physical structure. There is a wheelchair ramp to enter the building, which can be accessed from the lower parking lot on the side of the building, and a small elevator that serves that upper floors, which must be operated with the assistance of a Thomson House employee. For more details see here: https://pgss.mcgill.ca/en/thomson-house-accessibility .
